body_text.text:
The index case was identified in 32 of the 64 outbreaks analyzed (50%), but the source could not be identified in 26 outbreaks (40.63%) (Table 2
). Table 3
presents the numbers of patients and staff involved in the outbreaks, along with mortality stratified by the causative virus. In several reports, the fatality rate was not specified. Mortality was calculated based on number of deaths out of the total number of patients involved only when data were available. We identified 48 deaths out of 669 patients involved in 48 outbreaks. Mortality varied depending on the type of virus; overall average mortality was 7.17%, meaning that an average of 1 neonate died during each outbreak.
